NT|^B@2|cp|8|at| 
hondo717: |cp||at|On the play of the hand, as it was defended kia can make 4. He simply draws 4 rounds of trump, gets to dummy with the K of diamonds, and pitches his K of clubs on the spade. So he loses 2 spades and a diamond. That brings up another common defensive position that you should all know about. dee should play a 3rd round of spades, so that I trump the 10 of spades, depriving kia of a pitch.  This position comes up a lot. you cash one or two rounds of a suit setting up a card for the declaring side. However, when both your partner and declarer are out you should play a 3rd round to take away the winner from dummy, in this case the 10 of spades.|
