hondo717: |cp||at|We need to decide what we are playing over weak NT. I suggest either DONT or natural. I know some of you like Brozel.  My problem with Brozel is you cannot always compete at the 2 level with a 2 suited hand not containing hearts. I will discuss Brozel after the hand. I do not like Cappelletti either. Although many people play that over the weak NT. The reason is that you often have to go to the 3 level to find the best spot to play. For example, if you bid 2@H in Cappelletti, showing hearts and a minor, you have to go to the 3 level to play in the minor.|
PG| ***** 118 ***** |


NT|^B@2|cp|8|at|
hondo717: |cp||at|Let me just briefly go over Brozel, as that is another system that some use to compete over NT. It is similar in some ways to DONT, except it revolves around the heart suit. In Brozel, as with DONT, double is a single suited.  2@C shows clubs and hearts, 2@D shows diamonds and hearts, and 2@H shows hearts and spades.  2@S shows spades and a minor, and 2N shows both minors. So Brozel works well if you have hearts, in that, unlike DONT, partner always knows what 2 suits you have. However, DONT keeps you at a lower level if one of your 2 suits is not hearts.|
